communications.subject: Alabama Open Records Law Request: UAB/Lil John (Johnathan Smith) Concert Rider/Contract
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Alabama Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

A final copy of the concert rider and/or contract between University of Alabama at Birmingham and Lil John (Johnathan Smith) for his September 7, 2024 performance at Protective Stadium.
I am a student and this is for a class assignment.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

André Natta, a citizen of Alabama, in coordination with Braden Fine.

communications.subject: Maryland Public Information Act Request: Maryland Parole Release Rates (2023, 2024)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The total number of parole reviews conducted by the Maryland Parole Commission, including the total number of parole grants (approvals, releases, etc.) and the total number of parole denials (rejections, deferred, etc.). Please provide this data for 2023 (January 1 - December 31) and 2024 (January 1 - September 30). 

Note: Please do not include individual case summaries, only aggregate totals.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jacob Wourms
